# InvokeAI

## What this layer does

`InvokeAI` provides a browser-based image generation workspace exposed through the dedicated `image` layer.

This layer is paired with the pre-seeded model `${INVOKEAI_MODEL_TITLE}` from `${INVOKEAI_MODEL_REPO}` at revision `${INVOKEAI_MODEL_REVISION}`.

## How to access it

- Browser URL: `${INVOKEAI_URL}`
- Gateway username: `${INVOKEAI_GATEWAY_USER}`
- Gateway password: `${INVOKEAI_GATEWAY_PASSWORD}`

## Runtime notes

- The service is published only when the `image` layer is enabled.
- Model files are persisted inside a named Docker volume and scanned by InvokeAI on startup.
- The image layer remains separate from the chat-oriented `ai` layer based on Open WebUI and Ollama.

## Typical workflow

1. Start the lab with `atlas-lab up --with-image`
2. Open `${INVOKEAI_URL}`
3. Authenticate with the gateway credentials above
4. Use `${INVOKEAI_MODEL_TITLE}` as the default local image generation model
